14 SECTION 1.
15 (a) As used in this Act, the term:
16 (1) "Ad valorem taxes for educational purposes" means all ad valorem taxes for
17 educational purposes levied by, for, or on behalf of the Polk County school district,
18 including, but not limited to, any ad valorem taxes to pay interest on and to retire county
19 school district bonded indebtedness.
20 (2) "Homestead" means homestead as defined and qualified in Code Section 48-5-40 of
21 the O.C.G.A., as amended.
22 (b)(1) Each resident of the Polk County school district who is at least 65 years of age but
23 not yet 70 years of age on January 1 of the year in which application for the exemption
24 is made is granted an exemption on that person's homestead from Polk County school
25 district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the amount of the greater of 50
26 percent or $60,000.00 of the assessed value of that homestead. The value of that property
27 in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
28 (2) Each resident of the Polk County school district who is at least 70 years of age but
29 not yet 77 years of age on January 1 of the year in which application for the exemption
30 is made is granted an exemption on that person's homestead from Polk County school
31 district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in the amount of the greater of 75
32 percent or $80,000.00 of the assessed value of that homestead. The value of that property
33 in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
34 (3) Each resident of the Polk County school district who is at least 77 years of age or
35 older on January 1 of the year in which application for the exemption is made is granted
36 an exemption on that person's homestead from Polk County school district ad valorem
37 taxes for educational purposes in the amount of the full assessed value of that homestead
38 that does not exceed $500,000.00 appraised fair market value. The value of that property
39 in excess of such exempted amount shall remain subject to taxation.
