40 (4) In calendar year 2026, the maximum amount of homestead exemptions granted under
41 this Act shall not exceed $150 million in the aggregate annually. Upon the closing of the
42 books for the filing of homestead exemptions for such taxable year, the Polk County
43 governing authority or its designee shall calculate the aggregate amount of homestead
44 exemptions claimed under this Act for such taxable year. If such total is equal to or less
45 than $150 million in the aggregate for that taxable year, then each senior citizen claiming
46 a homestead exemption under this Act shall receive the full value of such exemption. If
47 the total exceeds $150 million in the aggregate for that taxable year, the governing
48 authority or its designee shall calculate the amount by which the total exceeds $150
49 million and shall reduce the amount of homestead exemptions claimed by such senior
50 citizens in an amount equal to such difference so that the total amount of homestead
51 exemptions being claimed under this Act for such taxable year shall equal $150 million.
52 Such reduction shall be applied on proportionate basis.
53 (c) A person shall not receive any homestead exemption granted by subsection (b) of this
54 section unless such person or person's agent files an application with the tax commissioner
55 of Polk County, giving such person's age and such additional information relative to
56 receiving such exemption as will enable the tax commissioner of Polk County to make a
57 determination regarding the initial and continuing eligibility of such person for such
58 exemption. The tax commissioner of Polk County shall provide application forms for this
59 purpose.
60 (d) The exemptions shall be claimed and returned as provided in Code Section 48-5-50.1 of
61 the O.C.G.A., as amended. The exemptions shall be automatically renewed from year to year
62 so long as the person granted a homestead exemption under subsection (b) of this section
63 occupies the residence as a homestead. After such person has filed the proper application as
64 provided in subsection (c) of this section, it shall not be necessary to make application
65 thereafter for any year, and such exemption shall continue to be allowed to such person. It
66 shall be the duty of any such person granted a homestead exemption under subsection (b) of
