75 SECTION 2.
76 In accordance with the requirements of Article VII, Section II of the Constitution of the State
77 of Georgia, this Act shall not become law unless it receives the requisite two-thirds' majority
78 vote in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.
79 SECTION 3.
80 The election superintendent of Polk County shall call and conduct an election as provided
81 in this section for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of the Polk County school
82 district for approval or rejection. The election superintendent shall conduct that election on
83 the Tuesday after the first Monday in November of 2025 and shall issue the call and conduct
84 that election as provided by general law. The election superintendent shall cause the date and
85 purpose of the election to be published once a week for two weeks immediately preceding
